在[[英國|英國]]，'''國會議員'''（{{lang-en|Member of Parliament}}，縮寫：MP），是透過全民直接選舉產生的[[英国下议院|下議院議員]]，每名都是各自在[[英國國會選區|650個其中一個的國會選區]]以[[領先者當選|領先者當選制]]當選。《[[英國定期國會法|2011年定期國會法]]》規定除列明情況外，下議院須最少每五年改選一次，所以每名國會議員的每屆任期最多亦為五年。

[[英國上議院|上議院]]雖然是[[英国议会|國會]]構成的一部分，但該院的議員並不會被稱爲國會議員，僅為上議院議員（{{lang|en|Member of the House of Lords}}）。

== 職責 ==
根據[[温斯顿·丘吉尔|温斯顿·丘吉尔]]所撰的《國會議員的職責》<ref name="hop">{{cite web|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200607/cmselect/cmmodern/337/33706.htm|title=House of Commons – Modernisation of the House of Commons – First Report|publisher=Parliament of the United Kingdom|language=en|accessdate=2020-10-08|archive-date=2020-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101143031/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200607/cmselect/cmmodern/337/33706.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，國會議員首要的責任是謹以至誠、不偏不倚地，作保存聯合王國榮譽和安全的決定。第二才是對選民負責，國會議員是被選民選作他們的代表（{{lang|en|representative}}），不是受他們委派的人（{{lang|en|delegate}}）。最為次要的責任則是對政黨的團體或計劃負責。國會議員都應該要有這三種忠誠，但任何一個健康民主體制的體現在於，國會議員毋庸置疑能按這個次序行事。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/politics/brexit-deal-theresa-may-parliament-constitution-commons-vote-mps-a8797151.html|title=Fixing Brexit: How parliament's checks and balances can solve our political crisis|date=1 March 2019|website=The Independent|language=en|accessdate=2020-10-08|archive-date=2020-10-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201012063000/https://www.independent.co.uk/politics/brexit-deal-theresa-may-parliament-constitution-commons-vote-mps-a8797151.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bL0FDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT45&lpg=PT45&dq=%22representative+but+not+the+delegate%22|title=Political Parties and Elections: Legislating for Representative Democracy|first=Anika|last=Gauja|date=22 April 2016|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781317078722|via=Google Books|language=en|access-date=2020-10-08|archive-date=2020-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805231646/https://books.google.com/books?id=bL0FDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT45&lpg=PT45&dq=%22representative+but+not+the+delegate%22|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vTff_YwkKSYC&pg=PA8&lpg=PA8&dq=%22representative+but+not+the+delegate%22|title=Revitalising the Chamber: the role of the back bench Member, first report of session 2006–07, report, together with formal minutes, oral and written evidence|first=Great Britain: Parliament: House of Commons: Select Committee on Modernisation of the House of|last=Commons|date=20 June 2007|publisher=The Stationery Office|isbn=9780215034670|via=Google Books|language=en|access-date=2020-10-08|archive-date=2020-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805231733/https://books.google.com/books?id=vTff_YwkKSYC&pg=PA8&lpg=PA8&dq=%22representative+but+not+the+delegate%22|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=89AYDQAAQBAJ&pg=PT1001&lpg=PT1001&dq=%22representative+but+not+the+delegate%22|title=Classic Readings and Cases in the Philosophy of Law|first=Susan|last=Dimock|date=16 September 2016|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781315509631|via=Google Books|language=en|access-date=2020-10-08|archive-date=2020-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200811184740/https://books.google.com/books?id=89AYDQAAQBAJ&pg=PT1001&lpg=PT1001&dq=%22representative+but+not+the+delegate%22|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/2017/02/03/churchill-would-have-defended-enemies-democracy/|title=Why Churchill would have defended our 'enemies of democracy'|first=Michael|last=Deacon|date=3 February 2017|work=The Telegraph|language=en|accessdate=2020-10-08|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111221848/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/2017/02/03/churchill-would-have-defended-enemies-democracy/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 議席空缺 ==
如出現議席空缺，若非大選臨近，該選區則需為餘下任期舉行補選。國會議員是不能以任何原因成功提出請辭的，離任議席的唯一方法是因「擔任會接受[[英国君主|君主]]收益的職位」（{{lang|en|{{le|有收益的職位|Office of profit|office of profit}} under the Crown}}）而被剝奪出任國會議員的資格，故此產生了現代[[英國下議院議員辭職方式|國會議員的辭職方式]]。另外，{{le|1981年人民代表法|Representation of the People Act 1981}}規定，任何現任國會議員如被判處一年或以上監禁，將立即離任。{{le|2015年罷免國會議員法|Recall of MPs Act 2015}}授權選民，按國會議員的某些輕微違法行為去聯署罷免請願書，如同一國會選區內超過百分之十的選民參與聯署該罷免請願書，該選區議席亦會被騰空。

== 參選資格 ==
參選國會議員只有兩個條件。參選人需要年滿18歲，以及是[[英國國籍法|英國公民]]（不需要持英國國籍）、或是[[英联邦|英聯邦成員國公民]]、或是[[爱尔兰|愛爾蘭共和國公民]]。參選人不需要登記作選民，亦不需要是參選選區的居民。<ref name="el">{{Cite web|url=https://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/sites/default/files/pdf_file/UKPGE-Part-1-Can-you-stand-for-election.pdf|title=UK Parliamentary general election, Guidance for candidates and agents, Part 1 of 6 – Can you stand for election?|website=Electoral Commission|language=en|accessdate=2020-10-08|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111223339/https://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/sites/default/files/pdf_file/UKPGE-Part-1-Can-you-stand-for-election.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="el_NI" >{{Cite web|url=https://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/sites/default/files/2019-09/UKPGE-Part%201-Can%20you%20stand%20for%20election-Northern-Ireland_1.pdf|title=UK Parliamentary general election – Northern Ireland, Guidance for candidates and agents, Part 1 of 6 – Can you stand for election?|website=Electoral Commission|language=en|accessdate=2020-10-08|archive-date=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804013951/https://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/sites/default/files/2019-09/UKPGE-Part%201-Can%20you%20stand%20for%20election-Northern-Ireland_1.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

然而，按照{{le|1975年下議院取消資格法|House of Commons Disqualification Act 1975}}，以下人士在所有國會選區並沒有參選資格：
*[[英国文官队伍|內務文官]]（即公務員，但不包括外交官）
*{{le|英國執法部門|Law enforcement in the United Kingdom|警務人員}}
*[[英國軍隊|正規部隊服役的軍人]]（不包括[[海軍元帥_(英國皇家海軍)|海軍元帥]]、[[英国陆军元帅列表|陸軍元帥]]和[[英国空军元帅列表|空軍元帥]]）
*[[威爾斯議會|威爾斯議會議員]]和[[北愛爾蘭議會|北愛爾蘭議會議員]]（不包括[[蘇格蘭議會|蘇格蘭議會議員]]）
*[[英國上議院|上議院議員]]，以及
*[[英國司法機構|法官]]等等。

此外，破產人士以及正在服一年或以上刑期的在囚人士亦不能參選。<ref name="el"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.uk/commons/lib/research/notes/snpc-03221.pdf|title=Disqualification for membership of the House of Commons|date=13 October 2004|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060321002524/http://www.parliament.uk/commons/lib/research/notes/snpc-03221.pdf|archive-date=2006-03-21|language=en|accessdate=2020-10-08|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

